'''H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze''' (born 23 February 1967), is a French chef. She has held two [[Michelin star]]s at one time or another in each of her two restaurants, [[H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze at The Connaught]] in London, and [[Restaurant H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze]] in Paris.

==Career==
In 1990 she began working for [[Alain Ducasse]] in the office of the [[Louis XV (restaurant)|Louis XV]] restaurant in Monaco,<ref name=catinterview2011/> after graduating from University. She was convinced to enter the kitchen by Ducasse;<ref name=superchefmail2009 /> it was her only time working elsewhere than her family restaurant, and later said that she was working in the office about half the time.<ref name=standardmad2011 /> After working for Ducasse for three years, she returned to her family's restaurant and kept it's existing [[Michelin star]]. After the restaurant closed in 1999 after suffering from financial difficulties,<ref name=superchefmail2009 /> she opened [[Restaurant H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze]] in Paris in 1999, and won her first Michelin star in 2001, and picked up a second in 2003.<ref name=namedlondon/> The second star was lost in the 2010 version of the guide.<ref name=awardstwostars>{{cite news|last=K<U+00FC>hn|first=Kerstin|title=Michelin awards two stars to H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze|url=http://www.caterersearch.com/Articles/25/01/2011/336622/Michelin-awards-two-stars-to-H233l232ne-Darroze.htm|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Caterer and Hotelkeeper|date=18 January 2011}}</ref>

In 2008, she was named as the new chef at [[The Connaught]] in London, replacing [[Angela Hartnett]] who had operated [[Angela Hartnett at The Connaught]] there on behalf of [[Gordon Ramsay|Gordon Ramsay Holdings]]. Darroze took over as part of a <U+00A3>70m refurbishment of the hotel, and in addition to the restaurant, she is responsible for all catering for guests at the restaurant including room service.<ref name=namedlondon>{{cite news|last=Afiya|first=Amanda|title=H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze is named as the new chef at London<U+2019>s Connaught|url=http://www.caterersearch.com/Articles/26/03/2008/319768/hlne-darroze-is-named-as-the-new-chef-at-londons-connaught.htm|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Caterer and Hotelkeeper|date=26 March 2008}}</ref> [[H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze at The Connaught]], was panned by restaurant critics when it first opened.<ref name=standardmad2011>{{cite news|last=Cavendish|first=Lucy|title=H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze: two cities, two children and two Michelin stars. My mum says I'm insane|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/hlne-darroze-two-cities-two-children-and-two-michelin-stars-my-mum-says-im-insane-6561884.html|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Evening Standard|date=1 February 2011}}</ref> [[Food critic]] [[Jay Rayner]] described said of the food there, "Two of the very worst dishes ever to be served to me at this level".<ref>{{cite news|last=Rayner|first=Jay|title=The worst of times|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/lifeandstyle/2008/dec/14/jay-rayner-helene-darroze-the-connaught|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=The Observer|date=14 December 2008}}</ref> Despite this, the restaurant was awarded a Michelin star in 2009,<ref>{{cite web|title=Michelin stars in London|url=http://www.michelinonline.co.uk/travelshop/star-history/rg-lon.htm|publisher=Michelin Online|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref> and then a second star two years later in 2011.<ref name=catinterview2011/>

In 2012, she was admitted into the French [[Legion of Honour]] as a Chevalier (Knight) by President [[Nicolas Sarkozy]].<ref>{{cite news|title=H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze admitted into the French Legion of Honour|url=http://www.caterersearch.com/blogs/guide-girl/2012/01/helene-darroze-admitted-into-the-french-legion-of-honour.html|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Guide Girl|date=16 January 2012}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Darroze is a fourth generation chef, the previous three having run a family restaurant in [[Villeneuve-de-Marsan]], France. Before becoming a professional chef, she took a degree in business.<ref name=superchefmail2009>{{cite news|last=McCarthy|first=Fiona|title=French super chef H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze<U+2019>s secret Ingredient...|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/home/you/article-1204557/Freuch-super-chef-H-l-ne-Darroze-s-secret-Ingredient-.html|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=10 August 2009}}</ref> She was also the inspiration for the character Colette in [[Pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]]' 2007 film [[Ratatouille (film)|''Ratatouille'']].<ref name=superchefmail2009 />

She has two adopted daughters from Vietnam,<ref name=standardmad2011 /> Charlotte and Quiterie.<ref name=catinterview2011>{{cite news|last=K<U+00FC>hn|first=Kerstin|title=The Caterer Interview <U+2013> H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Darroze|url=http://www.caterersearch.com/Articles/27/04/2011/337945/the-caterer-interview-hlne-darroze.htm|accessdate=10 August 2012|newspaper=Caterer and Hotelkeeper|date=21 April 2011}}</ref> She alternatives on a weekly basis between staying in London and in Paris, in order to split her time between her two restaurants.<ref name=standardmad2011/>

